    {
      "id": 1,
      "text": "East Milton evolved from dense forests inhabited by indigenous peoples into a modern residential community.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        19
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.kupi.com/en-ae/explore/united-states/east-milton/history"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The first European settlers established homes along the Blackwater River in the early 1800s.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        20,
        22
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.kupi.com/en-ae/explore/united-states/east-milton/history"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "As timber demand rose, settlements pushed eastward, shaping the territory of present‑day East Milton.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        23
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.kupi.com/en-ae/explore/united-states/east-milton/history"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The 1882 completion of the Pensacola and Atlantic Railroad linked East Milton to major Gulf trade routes.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.kupi.com/en-ae/explore/united-states/east-milton/history"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The nearby NAS Whiting Field airfield turned East Milton into a comfortable suburb with developed infrastructure.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        28
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.kupi.com/en-ae/explore/united-states/east-milton/history"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "In 2019, a large‑scale expansion of State Road 87 made Gulf beaches more accessible to East Milton residents.",
